It was my high school graduation. I was serving as the senior class vice president who had the job of telling everyone to move their rope over their cap. I never got to practice for it so I went out their in front of everyone and their families and was given the opportunity to do so. I also graduated myself and being there with my parents was an ecstatic feeling.

Over the summer after high school, I was feeling down and without purpose. Maybe it was the thought that I was leaving my parents and going to college. I do not really know. The fact that one chapter of my life was over and another anew. I was pretty depressed. I would lay in bed every night and just listen to sad music and just tear up.

I was accepted to Duke through regular decision. My friends and I were driving down to Florida, and the results came out during the drive. I couldn't check because I was the driver, so I checked around six hours later when we stopped at Zaxby's. It was very exciting, and I called my parents who were driving in a different car.

I am taking the AP Physics 1 exam in one of my school buildings, It is me, my three classmates, and the proctor, who happens to be one of my school's counselors. I am very stressed, but I feel prepared.

Me collecting money through graphic designing over Covid-19 and getting enough money to buy a plane ticket to go to Egypt to pursue a research project since I couldn't do that in Saudi given the country's foreign policies for expatriate residents

column4: When I was 17, I attended a fencing tournament in Paris. The most vivid memories where mainly involving the stadium we competed in and its atmosphere. The stadium was huge, much larger than any place I have fenced in before and when the competitors, including me, were fencing, they would shut the lights off on the bleachers and shine them only on us. I remember this very well because it made me feel as if we were on TV or on display, and it made me fence much harder and filled me with pride.

A few months after I got my license, I was rushing to the gym and parked very quickly so I could get inside and get started. I am normally a fine driver but since I was in such a rush, I accidentally scratched a car while I was parking. I remember my heart dropping and being very nervous as this was my first experience getting into a "crash"(although not really a crash) and was unsure what to do. I waited for the owner of the car to come out and explained to them what happened. She was annoyed but was not rude in any way. She was in a hurry to pick her son up so we exchanged information and she left.

This one time at night, I was going to my parents' room to tell them something and I left and approached the kitchen. The second I was about halfway into the kitchen and almost to my room I felt something to my left side and I saw something move. I remember the left side of my body being cold and I got goosebumps. I didn't turn around and I ran to my room.

A scene that came to mind was when I lived in my old apartment a few years back. I was young and I remember showering in the bath and all of a sudden, an earthquake occurred. I remember being scared and yelling for my mom because it was the first earthquake I ever experienced.
I was swimming in my friend Jacob's pool with Hayes, Porter, Nash, and Jace. We ordered pizza and talked about our freshman year. Then we got out and watched a football game.
I was eating lunch with my friend Lila in Wu around noon. I got Ginger and Soy, and she had a salad. We talked about her work in sports and school.

Winning first place in anatomy at the state Science Olympiad tournament. I did a fist pump, feeling amazing that I had finally accomplished my goal of 4 years. A lot of my teammates were cheering and clapping.

I remember waking up in Korea when I was 3, and looking out across the city skyline as the sun rose. I was standing next to the kitchen counter at the top of 3 stairs that led down to the sitting area for eating.

In early March, I was accepted to one of the colleges that I was really interested in attending and it made me feel really good about my application and about my achievements up to that point in time.

When I was still in elementary or middle school, my dad hosted a holiday party at our house and had hired my piano teacher to provide entertainment using the piano we had. I was learning to play the saxophone and had learned some holiday songs for fun, so I did a duet with my piano teacher on the saxophone for the guests.
column6: Saxophone duet with my old piano teacher

column4: For my one-year anniversary with my ex-girlfriend, I remember taking her out to dinner at Bonefish Grill. I don't remember what entree I got, but we ordered a shrimp appetizer that was amazing. I remember feeling grateful and happy. After, we went to Liberty State Park on the Hudson River, and I remember getting mad at her because she was reading the directions and told me to take a wrong turn that ended up going towards New York City. We eventually made it there and walked along the waterfront. I remember us trying to find someone to take our picture, but I asked someone and she ignored/didn't hear me so I gave up because it was embarrassing. Overall, this is one of my happiest memories and one of the ones I thought most about during our relationship because even though it wasn't perfect, it was an extremely special night.

I went to the Nasher Museum last year to complete an assignment for my Writing 101 class with my friend Devin. It must have been first semester, since that's when I took Writing 101, but I can't remember exactly when. We went through one of the exhibits and took notes on the pieces on display. It was during the afternoon, probably late afternoon. I remember feeling bored and that the assignment was tedious and a waste of time.

In Twilight,  Jacob, in wolf form, was trying to defend Bella's being pregnant to the rest of the wolfpack. The wolfpack wanted to kill Bella and the legendary catastrophic halfbreed baby, but Jacob would not allow it. He was the orange-haired wolf while the rest was brown, grey, and white. The telepathic connection between the wolves causes a lot of voices to be produced. The pack's alpha, Sam the black-haired wolf, can bend the other wolves to his will. When he tried to invoke this ability against Jacob by snarling at him to force him to go with the pack, Jacob used all his might snarling back and said "I WILL NOT, I AM THE GRANDSON OF EPHRAIM BLACK. I AM THE SON OF A CHIEF. I WAS NOT MEANT TO FOLLOW YOU OR ANYBODY ELSE."

I walked past the track and said hi to a girl that introduced herself as Lida, and I dropped off my gear and walked over to the warmup space.

I went to the diner with my friends Julia, Gabi, and Saira one day in my senior year of high school. We walked out of school and were trying to decide where to go for lunch. I brought up going to the diner, and we walked over there. It was a cold day and I remember I was wearing a scarf. The diner was warm and I got a milkshake, turkey bacon, and pancakes.

I was on a road trip with my family and we were all chatting in the car. We were driving to Charleston, South Carolina to spend Thanksgiving and had just decided that we were going to have a no technology vacation. The sun was shining through the windshield and I could feel it on my face and a coldplay song was playing in the background.

I was in my dorm room studying for my chemistry midterm. The stress from that and being away from home made me feel isolated which led me to start crying.

In elementary school I really wanted a dog, but my dad was against it. So, everyday around 6:00 pm I would listen for the garage, to know when my dad was getting home. Before the garage was even completely open I would be on the other side waiting for my dad so that I could repeatedly ask for a dog. Eventually he got so annoyed that he said yes.
I got my coffee from the cafe at my school the other day, but I immediately dropped it on the ground. I was super embarrassed and rushed to clean it up, but never got another one.

The event that I think about often is the lacrosse championship game of my senior year. It was on May 13th at 6 pm at US Lacrosse Headquarters. We were playing against Glenelg Country School in the A conference championships, a team we previously lost to 23-2. After that lost we went from #1 in the country to #2 which was devastating because we knew we shouldn't have lost, but we had a lot of injured players that game. During the championship game, hundreds of people came including students, family, and faculty from both schools. The lights shined bright on us during the game and we would score back and forth the first 15 minutes of the game. But then we kept our intensity and focus and started to pull ahead. We kept this momentum the rest of the game and beat them by 7. I remember everyone storming the field to cheer with us and me holding the trophy. It was so significant to me because it was the last year and last game with some of my best friends and I got to lead my team as captain to a championship. We also remained the number 1 team in the country for the second year in a row.

Getting ready for my senior prom was very memorable and I think about it often. It was May 14, the day after winning the championship lacrosse game. I slept over my friends house because we had a party there after the game, but I had to wake up at 7 am to go to my hair appointment. i got a silk press with extensions and a side part. After that appointment I went home to eat and wait for the makeup artist to come and fix my face up. When she arrived, we sat in my kitchen doing my makeup. I had simple face makeup but I told her to add rhinestones along my eyelids to spice it up a little. I looked beautiful and after she left, i went to put on my dress. Of course my mom needed to take hundreds of pictures of me as we waited for my date to arrive to my house. He was very late because he lost his wallet which annoyed me because we didn't get to take many pictures but it was okay. He then drove us to the pre prom location where my friends and I would take more pictures before we left for prom.

My favorite activity at sleep away camp was water skiing.  When I was in the oldest age group I used to help the youngest campers during early morning ski.  There was one camper who was terrified of trying to water ski and refused to try for the first few weeks of camp.  Finally, after weeks of encouragement she agrred to try.  I got in the water to help support her.  As most people do, she fell a few times and did not get up on skis.  However, she looked at me and said "I'm not afraid anymore.  that wasnt too bad".  As an older camper that was one of the most rewarding experiences of my entire summer,.
column6: The emotions of learning to water ski

column4: I was shopping at my local gourmet market and ordered a 1/2 pound of artichoke hearts which were very expensive.  The woman helping me was probably about 70 years old.  When she handed me the container, I walked to the checkout area and joined the line.  About 5 minutes later I looked at the container and saw she had charged me for the wrong item and it was much less expensive than what I had ordered.  I wasn't sure whether to go back and tell her or just pay the cheaper price.  I thought about it for a few minutes and then finally decided to go back to the woman and tell her.  I felt a bit annoyed because the wait was already so long, but also didn't want to feel guilty about not paying the proper amount.

column4: I'm a few weeks pregnant and the only person who knows is my partner. We don't wish to keep the baby, but we haven't had the chance to follow through with the procedure. The cost is something we may not be able to cover, and its worries me that we won't be able to get the procedure done.

It was December 17th, 2023. The clock strikes 1pm and I freeze. I had been hysterically crying the whole day and it was time for the Duke Early Decision acceptances to be released. I was surrounded by my parents and I was too scared to press the button to see my fate. Through my tears, I looked at my parents and told them I was too nervous to look. They told me I had to, so I reluctantly pressed the "View Decision" button. Without even reading what it said, I saw confetti drop from the screen. I did it. I got into Duke University. I screamed and my parents hugged me. My dog jumped up on me and my nervous tears turned to happy ones. My dad threw confetti in the air as I screamed repeatedly "I'm going to Duke. Oh my gosh I'm going to Duke." Best day ever.

I was sitting in my dorm room when my friends come running to the door. It was around Halloween, so there was a bunch of decorations around my dorm in general. So, my friends coming running into my room and scream oh my gosh there was been a murder come outside and look at what happened. Everyone else who was in my room kind of stared at each other like what is going on. We all ran outside to for to find my friends had taken the halloween decorations from the lobby and made a crime scene outside my door. It was so funny and we all started hysterically laughing. The severed foot and hand they used still sits in my room to this day.
